data.name: Chipotle Chicken Burrito Bowl
data.quickTastyDescription: A flavorful and satisfying bowl packed with juicy chicken, rice, beans, and fresh toppings.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Season the chicken breast with chipotle seasoning and cook for about 7-8 minutes on each side until fully cooked.
While the chicken is cooking, prepare the rice according to package instructions.
In a bowl, layer the cooked rice, black beans, corn, and salsa.
Once the chicken is cooked, slice it and place it on top of the bowl.
Add shredded cheese, diced avocado, and a squeeze of lime juice on top.
data.modifiersForBase: Chicken, Rice, Beans, and Fresh Toppings
